{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Database Overview\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A database is a structured collection of data that allows for storing, managing, and retrieving information efficiently. Databases are crucial in various applications across industries, providing a foundation for data-driven decision-making and operations.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 Key Features of Databases\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Data Organization: Arranges data into structured formats such as tables to ensure efficient storage, retrieval, and manipulation.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Transaction Management: Ensures that all database operations are processed with full integrity, using ACID (Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability) properties.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Security: Enforces policies and techniques like authentication and encryption to protect data from unauthorized access and ensure privacy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Concurrency Control: Manages multiple users accessing the database simultaneously, preventing conflicts and ensuring data consistency.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Scalability: Supports the growth in data volume and user demand through techniques like vertical (scaling up) and horizontal (scaling out) scaling.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Backup and Recovery: Provides processes to recover data after loss or corruption, ensuring data is reliably restored to its last consistent state.\sa180\par}
